  "text": "• Lateral femoral cutaneous syndrome: Meralgia paresthetica is a rarely encountered sensory mononeuropathy characterized by paresthesia, pain or sensory impairment along the distribution of the lateral femoral cutaneous nerve (LFCN) caused by entrapment or compression of the nerve as it crosses the anterior superior iliac spine and runs beneath the inguinal ligament. Ultrasound-guided blockade of the LFCN is a safe and success technique to treat this condition [CITATION_1] 69) .",
